# UI Components & Design Guidelines

## shadcn/ui Components
Always use shadcn/ui components as building blocks. Available components are in `src/components/ui/`:

### Core Components
- [Card](mdc:src/components/ui/card.tsx) - For grouping related farming information
- [Button](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx) - Actions and navigation
- [Badge](mdc:src/components/ui/badge.tsx) - Status indicators for fields/tasks
- [Table](mdc:src/components/ui/table.tsx) - Data-heavy displays
- [Form](mdc:src/components/ui/form.tsx) - Field data entry

### Data Display
- [Chart](mdc:src/components/ui/chart.tsx) - Agricultural data visualization
- [Progress](mdc:src/components/ui/progress.tsx) - Task completion, crop growth
- [Avatar](mdc:src/components/ui/avatar.tsx) - User profiles, farmer photos

## Color Scheme (Agricultural Theme)
- **Primary**: Green shades for healthy crops/success (#22c55e, #16a34a, #15803d)
- **Secondary**: Earth tones (browns, amber) for soil/equipment
- **Warning**: Amber for attention needed (weather alerts, maintenance)
- **Error**: Red for critical issues (equipment failure, pest alerts)
- **Neutral**: Grays for secondary information

## Design Principles
- **Mobile-First**: Must work on tablets and phones in field conditions
- **Data Density**: Farmers need lots of information quickly accessible  
- **Clear Hierarchy**: Critical information (weather, alerts) should be prominent
- **Practical Colors**: Use colors that work in bright sunlight
- **Touch-Friendly**: Buttons and interactive elements sized for outdoor use

